Justice James Rika has recused himself from a case Nairobi Governor Mike Sonko filed challenging his impeachment. Sonko's lawyer accused the court of bias in this matter, insisting that the orders stopping the impeachment are still in force. However, county assembly lawyers said the orders have been vacated. Reports indicate that the judge recused himself after tempers flared in court on the issues related to the ongoing impeachment. The media was barred from entering the court. Lawyer Harrison Kinyanjui, acting for Sonko, said the judge recused himself without giving a reason. More follows...